16/12/2005
NEW YORK, United States -- Belgrade's co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal has deteriorated in recent months, chief UN prosecutor Carla del Ponte said in a statement to the UN Security Council on Thursday (15 December). She accused the Serbia-Montenegro military of blocking efforts to bring indictees to justice. Responding to her comments, Serbia-Montenegro Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic said they represent a final warning and show the international community is losing patience.Del Ponte was also critical of Bosnia and Herzegovina (Politika, Danas, Dnevni Avaz - 16/12/05; Reuters, AFP, DPA, B92, RTS, Beta, FENA - 15/12/05)
